regulatory road signs – other than the stop and give way signs – are generally circular, with (for prohibitions) a black symbol on a white background within a red border, or (for mandatory instructions) a white symbol on a blue background.
in some cases circular regulatory signs are placed on white rectangular panels together with text supplementing their meanings.
