site of confederate park // local businessman khleber m. van zandt organized the robert e. lee camp of the united confederate veterans in 1889. by 1900 it boasted more than 700 members.
the club received a 25-year charter to create the confederate park association in 1901, then purchased 373 acres (151 ha) near this site for the "recreation, refuge and relief of confederate soldiers" and their families.
