the university of texas press (or ut press) is a university press that is part of the university of texas at austin.
established in 1950, the press publishes scholarly books and journals in several areas, including latin american studies, texana, anthropology, u.s. latino studies, native american studies, african american studies, film & media studies, classics and the ancient near east, middle east studies, natural history, art, and architecture.
