bolívar has been depicted in opera, literature, film, and other media, and continues to be a part of the popular culture in many countries.
in 1883, to celebrate 100 years since his birth, the italian musician nicolò gabrielli composed the triumphal march simón bolívar and dedicated it to then president of venezuela antonio guzmán blanco.
